rk)", "file_type": "code", "source_file": "README.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "readme_psscriptanalyzer", "label": "PSScriptAnalyzer", "file_type": "code", "source_file": "README.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "readme_powershell", "label": "PowerShell 7+ (pwsh)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "README.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "readme_ssrs", "label": "SQL Server Reporting Services (SSRS)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "README.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "readme_pbirs", "label": "Power BI Report Server (PBIRS)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "README.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "readme_security_model", "label": "Integrated Windows security model", "file_type": "rationale", "rationale": "Every connection runs as the current Windows identity; SQL (dbatools) and REST (ReportingServicesTools / Invoke-RestMethod -WebSession) use the caller's own credentials so there are no SQL logins, passwords, or external secret store. The only secret is the encryption-key password, never stored in .env, passed as a [SecureString] -KeyPassword and prompted interactively (Read-Host -AsSecureString) when omitted.", "source_file": "README.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "readme_transfer_model", "label": "SMB fileshare transfer model", "file_type": "rationale", "rationale": "Backups move over SMB fileshares, not any cloud object store. Phase 2 backs up .bak files to the source share, phase 3 copies them share-to-share, phase 4 restores from the target share keeping original DB names. Share roots and file names are always separate inputs so the cmdlets join <share>+<file> themselves and no full path is ever hard-coded.", "source_file": "README.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "readme_encryption_key", "label": "Encryption key (.snk)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "README.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "readme_dry_run", "label": "Dry run (read-only rehearsal)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "README.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "readme_runbook", "label": "Nine-phase migration runbook", "file_type": "concept", "rationale": "Invoke-RsMigration sequences nine phases in-process (no child processes) in order, aborting on the first failure and throwing a terminating error naming the failing phase so a non-zero result identifies exactly where it stopped.", "source_file": "README.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "readme_quality_gate", "label": "Quality gate (>=90% coverage)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "README.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "readme_idempotent_refresh", "label": "Idempotent subscription refresh", "file_type": "rationale", "rationale": "Each subscription is keyed on its content (owner, path, schedule, delivery) not its server-assigned Id, so re-running the import updates an existing match in place instead of creating a duplicate, making the step safe to repeat. Selective import via an -IncludeSubscription allow-list; empty means import all.", "source_file": "README.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": 